    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nFollow up to this thread: https://groups.google.com/g/cython-users/c/pItc3SdjrpY\r\n\r\nFor parallel-code involving memoryviews we have a significant performance degredation due to re-acquiring the GIL in `__Pyx_ErrOccurredWithGIL` during various memoryview operations. See the following performance graph snippet taken from perf on linux:\r\n\r\n```\r\n               |          |          |--11.20%--__Pyx_CyFunction_Vectorcall_FASTCALL_KEYWORDS\r\n               |          |          |          __pyx_pw_5pyFAI_3ext_10splitPixel_13fullSplit1D_engine\r\n               |          |          |          __pyx_pf_5pyFAI_3ext_10splitPixel_12fullSplit1D_engine\r\n               |          |          |          |          \r\n               |          |          |           --11.19%--__pyx_memoryview_copy_contents\r\n               |          |          |                     |          \r\n               |          |          |                     |--10.30%--__Pyx_ErrOccurredWithGIL\r\n               |          |          |                     |          PyGILState_Ensure\r\n               |          |          |                     |          PyEval_RestoreThread\r\n               |          |          |                     |          |          \r\n               |          |          |                     |          |--4.71%--0x7f64ba908a68\r\n               |          |          |                     |          |          |          \r\n               |          |          |                     |          |           --4.70%--___pthread_cond_timedwait (inlined)\r\n               |          |          |                     |          |                     |          \r\n               |          |          |                     |          |                     |--1.33%--__pthread_mutex_cond_lock\r\n               |          |          |                     |          |                     |          |          \r\n               |          |          |                     |          |                     |           --0.87%--__GI___lll_lock_wait\r\n               |          |          |                     |          |                     |          \r\n               |          |          |                     |          |                     |--0.59%--__futex_abstimed_wait_common\r\n```\r\n\r\n(This is truncated a little based on what was easy to copy, but it illustrates the point).\r\n\r\nThe upshot is that the memoryview utility code is using our new exception handling semantics, and generating code that's really poor outside the GIL (because it always needs an error check).\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n_No response_\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nThe old performance\n\n### OS\n\nLinux\n\n### Python version\n\n_No response_\n\n### Cython version\n\n3.0.0a11\n\n### Additional context\n\n1. I'll produce a fix for this shortly - having identified the problem it's pretty easy to fix.\r\n2. I still think that needing `__Pyx_ErrOccurredWithGIL` is a real performance pitfall (see link to previous discussion https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/5310#discussion_r1133241920). Although it's not strictly an user error, I think we should warn about it in some conditions (e.g. when needed in `nogil` code I'd suggest)",
